# README
- this is a simple research pipeline example
- it allows to run the entire process from data preparation to a ready-to-submit manuscript including references etc.
- it allows this entire process to be run without ever switching software 
- it allows the entire process to be easily reproduced with alternative cut-offs, definitions, subsets etc.
- it is perfectly suited to accomodate both:
1. to be run on small samples for the sake of speed and simplicity 
2. to be run in batch mode settings (i.e. National Safe Haven settings) when the process is time and memory consuming
- for server setups, we typically need to find a work-around for pandoc when creating our final output
- work-arounds for apache/guacamole settings will be presented in a later example 
